<p>South Africa and the United States are locked in a diplomatic spat as President Trump’s administration boycotts the G20 summit in Johannesburg, the first hosted on African soil, and proposes sending only a lower-level representative to the handover event for the U.S.-hosted summit [npr.org#1][dw.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Pretoria has objected, saying it will not conduct the presidency handover to a junior official, while the White House insists the boycott stands and any broader participation is off the table [theguardian.com#1][allafrica.com#1][semafor.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Despite tensions, envoys have reached a draft leaders’ declaration without U.S. input, and South Africa aims to focus the meeting on global inequality and debt restructuring/debt relief [theglobeandmail.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][pbs.org#1][semafor.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/7pAYoJqpUtHYv-ONEAV71erC6h1j0OX6h7I58mm8RcljgwiKZUolMA_H3OmWjz_u4k1BiuejDfcb8WGrKPd4VZGq8uXFn5Bz1TId7ht4Wc4H' alt='Banners of G20 leaders displayed near the Johannesburg summit venue ahead of the November 22–23 meeting.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Boycott stance: The White House says the U.S. will boycott the Johannesburg G20 over disputed claims of discrimination in South Africa and will only send its ambassador to the handover ceremony, not to summit talks [thehindu.com#1][semafor.com#1][firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Handover row: South Africa says it will not conduct the G20 presidency handover to a junior U.S. embassy official and seeks top-level representation for the ceremony [theguardian.com#1][allafrica.com#1].</li><li>Historic first: The summit is the first G20 held on African soil, with hosts aiming to prioritize debt restructuring and global inequality on the agenda [dw.com#1][pbs.org#1][semafor.com#1].</li><li>Draft declaration: G20 envoys agreed on a draft leaders’ declaration without U.S. input, including references to climate change [theglobeandmail.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1].</li><li>Wider frictions: Beijing declined a leaders’ meeting with Tokyo on the sidelines, and several leaders besides President Trump are skipping, including those of Argentina, China, Indonesia, and Mexico [scmp.com#2][semafor.com#2][semafor.com#1].</li><li>Civic voices: South African women staged protests in Johannesburg spotlighting gender-based violence ahead of the summit [nytimes.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][time.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. administration: Maintains a full boycott of the summit, saying only its ambassador will attend the handover ceremony and denying any reversal as “fake news.” [thehindu.com#1][semafor.com#1] (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/us-denies-ending-south-africa-g20-boycott/article70306879.ece'>The Hindu; Semafor</a>)</li><li>South African government: Objects to a junior U.S. representative for the handover and says the country “will not be bullied.” [theguardian.com#1][allafrica.com#1][firstpost.com#2] (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/21/run-up-to-g20-in-south-africa-marred-by-hosts-simmering-row-with-us'>The Guardian; AllAfrica; Firstpost</a>)</li><li>European Union: Sees an opportunity to fill the void and deepen commercial ties amid the U.S. absence [dw.com#1] (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/g20-south-africa-hosts-summit-in-shadow-of-us-boycott/a-74843303'>DW</a>)</li><li>G20 envoys: Reached a draft leaders’ declaration without U.S. input, including climate language [theglobeandmail.com#1][straitstimes.com#1] (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-g20-draft-leaders-declaration-climate-change/'>The Globe and Mail; The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>China and Japan: Diplomatic rift persists as Beijing declined a leaders’ meeting with Tokyo at the summit [scmp.com#2] (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3333666/us-boycott-and-china-japan-rift-loom-large-leaders-gather-g20-summit'>SCMP</a>)</li><li>South African civil society: Protesters use the summit spotlight to demand action on gender-based violence and femicide [abcnews.go.com#1][nytimes.com#1] (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/south-african-women-stage-lie-protest-gender-based-127753051'>ABC News; New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/21/run-up-to-g20-in-south-africa-marred-by-hosts-simmering-row-with-us'>South Africa’s dispute with US escalates amid row over G20 handover event</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/opinion/world-opinion/article/3333596/multilateralism-isnt-dead-despite-trumpian-year'>Trump’s G20 boycott sums up a year of US attacks on multilateralism</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/21/nx-s1-5615174/south-africa-g20-us-boycott'>South Africa hosts G20 as tensions with U.S. flare amid boycott</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202511210316.html'>South Africa: Ramaphosa Refuses to Hand Over G20 to US Junior Official</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://www.semafor.com/article/11/21/2025/us-denies-reneging-on-its-boycott-of-g20'>US denies reneging on its boycott of G20</a> - semafor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/us-denies-ending-south-africa-g20-boycott/article70306879.ece'>U.S. denies ending South Africa G20 boycott</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/g20-summit-us-boycott-south-africa-trump-withdrawal-13952740.html'>Why is Trump boycotting Africa&#x27;s first G20 summit in Johannesburg?</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/g20-south-africa-hosts-summit-in-shadow-of-us-boycott/a-74843303'>G20: South Africa hosts summit in shadow of US boycott</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956461/modi-heads-to-south-africa-for-g20-summit-boycotted-by-trump'>Modi heads to South Africa for G20 summit boycotted by Trump</a> - dawn.com</li><li><